---
import LandingLayout from '../../layouts/LandingLayout.astro';
---

<LandingLayout title="Dragon Railway — RamBros 3D" description="The world's largest collection of 3D printed model trains. Open source S-scale 3D printable model railway ecosystem." docsLink="/dragon/">

<section class="py-24 px-4">
	<div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
		<img src="/rambros/dragon-railway-logo/dragon-railway.png" alt="Dragon Railway" class="w-32 md:w-40 mx-auto mb-8 drop-shadow-lg" />
		<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-4" style="font-family: 'Belanosima', sans-serif;">Dragon Railway</h1>
		<p class="text-xl text-base-content/60 mb-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">The world's largest collection of 3D printed model trains.</p>
		<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 text-sm text-base-content/50">
			<span class="badge badge-outline">S-scale (1/64)</span>
			<span class="badge badge-outline">Open Source</span>
			<span class="badge badge-outline">Fully 3D Printed</span>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="py-16 px-4">
	<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
		<div class="text-center mb-16">
			<p class="text-primary font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase text-sm mb-3">What Is It</p>
			<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">An Open Ecosystem</h2>
			<p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
				The Dragon Railway is an open-source <strong>3D printable model railway ecosystem</strong> in S-scale (1/64). A highly detailed and accurate scale model of a railway system — complete with locomotives, wagons, tracks, control systems, and accessories. Every major component is designed to be printed on a standard FDM printer.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="bg-base-200 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10 mb-16">
			<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
				<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-primary"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
				Fully 3D Printed
			</h3>
			<p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
				As we say — <strong>"If it can be 3D printed, it will be 3D printed."</strong> From the body and wheels to the couplers, every major component is 3D printed. The only additional parts you need are screws, bearings, O-rings, and electronics. That's it.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="py-16 px-4">
	<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
		<div class="text-center mb-16">
			<p class="text-primary font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase text-sm mb-3">Our Journey</p>
			<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">From Idea to Ecosystem</h2>
			<p class="text-base-content/60 max-w-xl mx-auto">Three years of iteration, failure, and improvement. Every version taught us something new.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="relative">
			<div class="absolute left-6 md:left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-px bg-base-content/20 -translate-x-1/2"></div>

			<div class="relative flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 mb-16">
				<div class="md:w-1/2 md:pr-12 md:text-right pl-16 md:pl-0">
					<div class="text-primary font-bold text-sm tracking-wide mb-2">2022 — The Beginning</div>
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">HO Scale Origins</h3>
					<p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
						Dragon Railway first started as an HO scale project. We wanted to build a fully 3D printed railway system, but after extensive testing, we concluded it was <strong>too unreliable</strong> on FDM printers. So we pivoted to <strong>1/64 scale</strong> — and everything clicked.
					</p>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/50">
						The original HO scale designs are still available: <a href="https://github.com/DragonRailway/ho-scale-v0" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary underline">GitHub repository</a>
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="absolute left-6 md:left-1/2 w-3 h-3 bg-primary rounded-full -translate-x-1/2 mt-1 ring-4 ring-base-200/30"></div>
				<div class="md:w-1/2 md:pl-12 pl-16"></div>
			</div>

			<div class="relative flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 mb-16">
				<div class="md:w-1/2 md:pr-12 md:text-right pl-16 md:pl-0 order-2 md:order-1"></div>
				<div class="absolute left-6 md:left-1/2 w-3 h-3 bg-primary rounded-full -translate-x-1/2 mt-1 ring-4 ring-base-200/30"></div>
				<div class="md:w-1/2 md:pl-12 pl-16 order-1 md:order-2">
					<div class="text-primary font-bold text-sm tracking-wide mb-2">Early 2023 — V1 Launch</div>
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">First Release</h3>
					<p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
						Dragon Railway V1 launched as a fully open-source 3D printed model railway system. Locomotives, wagons, a unique parametric track design, and an autocoupler system — all printable at home. The collection has steadily grown into the largest 3D printed model train ecosystem available today.
					</p>
					<img src="/images/image.png" alt="Dragon Railway V1" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-4 w-full" />
					<div class="aspect-video w-full rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg mb-4">
						<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SFDSUE1-vPA" title="Dragon Railway V1" frameborder="0" class="w-full h-full" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
					</div>
					<a href="https://www.printables.com/@rambros/collections/406299" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">View Full Collection on Printables</a>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="relative flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 mb-16">
				<div class="md:w-1/2 md:pr-12 md:text-right pl-16 md:pl-0">
					<div class="text-primary font-bold text-sm tracking-wide mb-2">Late 2024 — V2</div>
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Expanding the Fleet</h3>
					<p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
						V2 built on the foundation of V1 by expanding the range of models available. More locomotives, more wagons, more track configurations — most open source with the same collaborative spirit that made V1 successful.
					</p>
					<div class="aspect-video w-full rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg">
						<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LkO8dfGma0c" title="Dragon Railway V2" frameborder="0" class="w-full h-full" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="absolute left-6 md:left-1/2 w-3 h-3 bg-primary rounded-full -translate-x-1/2 mt-1 ring-4 ring-base-200/30"></div>
				<div class="md:w-1/2 md:pl-12 pl-16"></div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="py-16 px-4">
	<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
		<div class="text-center mb-12">
			<p class="text-primary font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase text-sm mb-3">Recognition</p>
			<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Featured in the Media</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
			<img src="/images/image-1.png" alt="Dragon Railway media feature" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full" />
			<img src="/images/image-2.png" alt="Dragon Railway media feature" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full" />
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="py-16 px-4">
	<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
		<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Support the Project</h2>
		<p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed mb-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
			If you find this project interesting, <strong>please share it with your friends</strong> and anyone who might like it. The sustainability of Dragon Railway relies on <strong>community engagement</strong> — more people means more ideas, feedback, and resources.
		</p>
		<p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
			A thriving community ensures we can keep delivering new models, updates, and enhancements — making Dragon Railway a lasting resource for model train makers around the globe.
		</p>
		<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
			<a href="https://www.printables.com/@rambros/collections/406299" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Browse Collection</a>
			<a href="https://github.com/DragonRailway" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">GitHub</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

</LandingLayout>
